      <div class="callout-title">📚 Chapter Overview</div>
      <p>Multimodal AI systems process and understand multiple types of data—text, images, audio, video. This chapter covers vision-language models, cross-modal understanding, and state-of-the-art multimodal systems.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="callout info">
      <div class="callout-title">📌 Learning objectives</div>
      <ul>
        <li>Define multimodal AI and explain why combining modalities changes what models can do</li>
        <li>Describe CLIP at a conceptual level (joint embeddings via contrastive learning) and what it enables</li>
        <li>Explain the common VLM pattern: vision encoder → projection → LLM over visual + text tokens</li>
